00:32:54.720 --> 00:32:56.240
how to have a JIT,

00:32:56.740 --> 00:32:58.740
but still do all the compiler stuff at build time.

00:32:59.480 --> 00:33:01.660
So when you build this copy and patch JIT,

00:33:01.720 --> 00:33:04.560
you actually need LLVM, but only at build time.

00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:05.960
And then it can go away.

00:33:06.080 --> 00:33:07.700
And so the person who receives the interpreter

00:33:07.960 --> 00:33:08.740
doesn't need LLVM anymore.

00:33:09.420 --> 00:33:15.020
